name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Iowa State! Delayed at O’Hare but finally taking off. We’ll be a little late, but really looking forward to seeing you in Ames tonight!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: In just 18 days, you've proven the power of people everywhere joining together to run a true grassroots campaign: ✅$9.4 million raised ✅218,000 contributions ✅98% of donations under $200 ✅99% of fundraising via online ✅$0 from PACs, special interests, lobbyists &corporations

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: On #TransDayOfVisibility, let's send a clear signal to our past, current, and future transgender service members who put their lives on the line for our country. We see you, we appreciate you, and we will fight to ensure your service is honored and welcomed.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: On Cesar Chavez Day and each day after it, let's remember, honor, and continue his work advocating for labor rights, civil rights, and human rights.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: An update: refugees & asylum seekers are no longer being trapped under the PDN Bridge. That cruelty has ended but questions into how we're treating our fellow human beings or why it occurred in the 1st place should not. There must be accountability for actions taken in our name.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "His ambitious, progressive agenda included promoting greater voter participation by ending gerrymandering...He would also end the prohibition of marijuana and curb the school-to-prison pipeline that severely impacts communities of color."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Together, as one country united, we can fulfill the promise of America, to ourselves, to each other, and to every generation that succeeds us.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: I am honored to run to serve you as President of the United States; and I am grateful to each one of you who will join this campaign and commit yourself in service to this great country of ours.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Our ability to campaign this way as a campaign run for & by people - no PACs, no corporations - people from every state & territory — can bring us together not just in defeating Trump, but in ensuring that we have the full power of people to accomplish this country’s priorities.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let us be clear: we will not be defined by our fears or the smallness of our differences; we will instead be known by our ambitions, our aspirations and the resolve, the creativity, the service and sacrifice by which we will have achieved them.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: El exito de este pais depende en el exito de cada persona en este pais.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Pero también necesitamos una economía donde todos pueden participar, y tener un prospecto de éxito independiente de su genero, de su raza, de los cuantas generaciones su familia tiene a dentro o aparte de los estados unidos.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Si queremos enfrentar los retos de cuidado de salud por todos; de la reforma migratoria; del cambio climático —necesitamos una democracia en que cada persona puede votar y ofrecer su voz.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The unprecedented concentration of wealth, power and privilege in the United States must be broken apart. Opportunity must be fully shared with all. We must all have the opportunity to succeed. Together. As one country.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let us also acknowledge that any hope of full political democracy must be premised on an unwavering pursuit of economic democracy. Every child must see a future for themselves in this country.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: So every citizen must be able to cast their vote, have their voice heard. We must sign into law a new voting rights act, we must forever banish big money from our politics, end gerrymandering, and enact same day voter registration in every part of the country.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: But if we want to do any of this — let us agree that our success as a country is based on the success of this democracy, the greatest mechanism devised to bring forth the power of people.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: This country can and must once again take its place as the indispensable leading nation, doing what no other country can, for ourselves and for the world.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: And when we talk about combatting climate change, it is important that this work ensures that every American benefits, including those poor and minority communities that have so often borne the brunt of climate change.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We have an opportunity now to meet an existential threat to this planet by ensuring that public health policy, economic policy, and the engine of a far more conscientious capitalism is put to work in service of our ability to meet this challenge of climate change.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let us organize this country around a historic effort to free this economy from a dependence on greenhouse gas emissions, invest in the technologies and jobs in renewable energy that will speed this transition, and reassert our international leadership before it is too late.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: And if the wars we are already in don't have a definition of victory or strategy to win them and bring these service members back home to their families and their communities, we must put an end to them.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let us not only ensure that we meet every single part of our obligation to our veterans but that we also make sure that before we enter yet another war that we have exhausted every single peaceful alternative.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: And if we’re serious about security, let this country of immigrants - republicans, independents and democrats  - rewrite our immigration laws in our own image, from our own experiences, and in the best traditions of this great country.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let’s ensure our security not through walls and militarization, but by investing in our ports of entry where the vast majority of everything and everyone that ever comes into this country first enters.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let’s not only honor our asylum laws and never again take another child from another parent at their most desperate and vulnerable moment, but guarantee that all separated families are reunited.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let’s bring millions more of our fellow Americans out of the shadows and on to a path to contribute even more to our country’s success.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: If we believe that this country’s success is premised on the fact that immigrants and asylum seekers from the world over have found a home here, then let us forever free Dreamers from any fear of deportation by making them U.S. citizens.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let’s end cash bail, private prisons, and the war on drugs. Let's confront the true legacy of slavery, of segregation, suppression, of how people have been criminalized & kept down based on their race and ethnicity. Only that truth will allow us to begin to repair the damage done

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: If we believe in real justice reform in the face of the largest prison population on the face of the planet — one disproportionately comprised of people of color — let us not just end the prohibition of marijuana but expunge the record of those arrested solely for possession.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let’s ensure everyone can succeed regardless of their family dynamics, their gender, their sexual orientation or their race. Paid family leave. Equal pay for women. No discrimination in the workplace, and access to capital for communities that have been shut out for generations.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let’s support rural America by listening to and partnering with rural communities on infrastructure, schools, hospitals, & broadband. Let’s make sure farmers can make a profit while they grow the food & fiber that feeds and clothes not just this country, but so much of the world.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let’s not diminish the power of unions in this country. Let's strengthen unions in this country and ensure a path to apprenticeships and careers. Guarantee that one job is enough by paying every working American a true living wage.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let’s graduate young women and men from high school who are career ready as well as college ready, able to pursue debt-free higher education or a job that provides purpose and a real paycheck. We can do this.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: If we believe in an economy that works for all, then let us invest in a world class Pre-k through 12 public education system and ensure that we are paying our educators a living wage so that they don’t have to work a second or third job.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: This means every one of us is able to afford our prescriptions, see a doctor, take our children to a therapist. No one priced out. No one denied care. No one left behind. Universal, guaranteed, high quality health care must be achieved as quickly and as surely as possible.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Universal healthcare means everyone gets primary healthcare, mental healthcare — and universal care also means that every woman makes her own decisions about her own body.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: If we believe in universal, guaranteed, high quality healthcare - because we see the consequences to our fellow Americans who go without - then let us come together around a solution.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: These challenges and the threats to our democracy cannot be met by half measures or with only half the country. It’s gonna take all we’ve got and it’s gonna take all of us.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The differences between us — where we live, who we love, to whom we pray, how long our families have been in this country, the color of our skin, the party to which we belong — those differences cannot be allowed to define us or divide us now. Let us be Americans first.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: A vigorous democracy - both economic and political - is the only check on the inertia of power, on the corruption and capture of our institutions, and the only means to elevate the voices and lives of our fellow Americans.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Unrestrained, money and influence have warped this country’s priorities and its very democracy. It has corrupted our democracy. It has invited cynicism, distrust and disengagement from Americans who see a government in thrall to those who can pay for access and outcomes.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: For too long in this country, the powerful have maintained their privilege at the expense of the powerless. They have employed fear and division — based on differences in race or ethnicity, geography and faith — to keep us apart, and angry and afraid of one another.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The challenges before us are the biggest of our lifetimes. Millions without healthcare; an economy that works too well for too few and not at all for too many; & the opportunity to avert the worst consequences of climate change fading in the face of our inaction. We must overcome

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Like so many of you, Amy and I have decided that at this moment of truth we must give it our all. This moment is our test - the generations that follow ours, the people of the future, are counting on us - and we cannot be found wanting.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: This is a campaign for America. For everyone in America. No one written off, no one taken for granted.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We don't back down in the face of Islamophobia and racism at home or abroad. We stand up, stand together and make it clear that terrorism won't be met with indifference but with action that honors our diversity as the people of the world. Thinking of our friends in New Zealand.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Really proud of Ron Stallworth, Spike Lee and the entire team behind BlacKkKlansman - courage over fear, love over hate. Felicidades Ron and Patsy, Spike Lee and team!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Tonight, we will meet lies and hate with the truth and a positive, inclusive, ambitious vision for the future from the U.S.-Mexico border. Join us: ➡️5:00 march at Bowie HS ➡️6:00 celebration of El Paso at Chalio Acosta Park

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: This cynical rhetoric of war, of invasions, of fear — totally disconnected from the truth — has led us to treat our fellow humans in the most inhumane way. And it hasn’t made us safer. We thought we could sacrifice some of our humanity for security, we risk losing both.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: And, by the way, none of this stuff has worked. As the border became more militarized, and deadlier, immigrants stopped returning to their home countries. In effect, this policy actually increased the number of undocumented immigrants in the U.S.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: “Yet, Mexicans nonetheless bore the brunt of the deportation campaign launched in the name of the war on terrorism, comprising 72 percent of those removed in 2009.”

name: Beto O'Rourke

name: Beto O'Rourke

name: Beto O'Rourke

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: You can also volunteer directly through Annunciation House. They're looking for people who are willing to drive refugees to the bus station and airport. To get started, email refugees@annunciationhouse.org and a volunteer lead will get back to you.

name: Beto O'Rourke

name: Beto O'Rourke

name: Beto O'Rourke

name: Beto O'Rourke

tweet: Goodnight from Waco! Hope to see you tomorrow in: 🚙Temple at 9:00 (3303 N 3rd St) 🚙Lampasas at 11:30 (1406 US-281) 🚙Horseshoe Bay at 3:00 (107 Twilight Lane) 🚙Austin at 5:30 (2015 E Riverside Dr)

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Good luck to all of the students, parents, teachers, and staff who are starting school today across Texas. Wishing you a great first day and an incredible new school year.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Hope to see you today in: 🚙Liberty at 9:30 (1816 Sam Houston St) 🚙Nacogdoches at 2:30 (317 E Main St) 🚙Longview at 5:30 (3700 Judson Rd)

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Tim we had a veterans town hall today in San Antonio and was thinking about you and our colleagues who have helped to make HVAC an example of successful bipartisanship, focusing on suicide reduction, access to care, housing and expediting appeals. Proud to serve with you!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Or when we have a nominee for a lifetime appointment on the Supreme Court who has weakened voting rights. We must use today's anniversary as a reminder of what John Lewis said while marching in Selma, "We’re not going back. We’re going to move forward."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The work is far from over when we still have racial gerrymandering, people being purged from the rolls, voter ID laws that are designed to make it more difficult for black voters to cast their ballots. When we have parts of the Voting Rights Act being invalidated piece by piece.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: On this day 53 years ago, LBJ signed the Voting Rights Act into law. It happened because people were willing to march, to protest, to be arrested, to put their lives on the line crossing the Edmund Pettus Bridge, to apply the pressure that formed the will to get it to his desk.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let's start by ending private prisons, mandatory minimums for minor drug offenses, the federal prohibition on marijuana, and the current system of cash bail that that punishes the poor.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: An update: One of the mothers we met with at the El Paso ICE detention center has been released, and flew to Tennessee where she is being reunited with her 3 children. 700+ left to be reunited. It's happening one at a time but it doesn't happen unless we keep the pressure on.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: All at a time when we have more student loan debt than credit card debt in this country.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: 1) Career Education Corporation reaches a $10 million settlement over defrauding students.  2) DeVos names 2 of their former executives as her senior counsel and senior adviser at our department of education.  3) The department changes guidance, puts corporations over students.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: More than 50,000 women are severely injured giving birth each year. About 700 mothers die. Half of these deaths could be prevented and half the injuries reduced or eliminated with better care.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: 28 years later, the ADA has helped get us closer to equal justice. Ensuring everyone can live to their full potential requires next steps, from protecting the ADA & passing the Disability Integration Act to creating greater access to the workforce for those with disabilities.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: That pregnant black women are dying at 2X the rate of pregnant white women. That black kids in preK-2nd grade were 5X more likely than white kids to receive a suspension. For K-12, 4X more likely. That by age 14, 1 out of 4 black kids have experienced a parent being imprisoned.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: James Baldwin once wrote "Not everything that is faced can be changed. But nothing can be changed until it's faced." Let's face head-on that unemployment is 2X higher for blacks than whites in TX. That white families have 10X more wealth than black families in America.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We all want newly confirmed VA Sec. Robert Wilkie to be successful. His success means we are better able to serve the women and men who served our country. I'm ready to work with him to reduce veteran suicide, enhance accountability, and deliver the care our veterans have earned.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Seeing kids who’ve just been reunited w parents but who are seemingly numb, not bonding, not connecting with their moms and dads. Clear that this has caused deep trauma for them. Grateful to the social workers, therapists and volunteers on site who are doing their best to help.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Clear that there is still not a firm plan in place for reunification. I get the sense local ICE office doing its best but in no way prepared for this level of industrial scale separation. No clear consistent means to track parents & kids once separated.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The press is not the enemy of the people.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Just days after the Justice department issued indictments for 12 Russian agents, agents who sought to undermine the genius of America — that 242 years in we are still able to govern ourselves and freely choose our leaders — the President chose a foreign power over the U.S.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The fact that the wealthiest, most powerful country in the world is abandoning our asylum laws. That our current immigration laws -- built on fear and cemented by characterizing immigrants as criminals, rapists, animals, an infestation -- don't reflect the reality on the ground.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: That we can make our immigration laws and enforcement more humane. We should start by using the House, the world's most deliberative body, to talk about real crises facing our country. The fact that more than 2,500 kids remain separated from their parents after we took them away.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: I don’t support the abolishment of ICE, but it’s wrong to pass leg that praises some of the practices that need reform. Those of us who call the border home, including ICE officers & border patrol agents who live in our communities, know we can do better than current policies.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Voted on a cynical bill to give a blanket endorsement to the practices of ICE. While doing nothing to reunite kids w/ parents or address legitimate concerns about practices within ICE, it did condone militarization of the border & the admin’s zero tolerance policies. I voted NO.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "The solution to the problem Trump created starts with treating people like they're people, not like animals, as he called them recently. Start with that, and the solution to what looks now like an unsolvable problem will follow." -Corpus Christi Caller Times

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "This is a human rights emergency of Trump's creation. Not only did he and his lieutenants choose separation of parents from children as a deliberately cruel cudgel...but they did it with no discernible plan for reuniting the children with their families."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We need to expand Medicaid to cover more Texans including vulnerable children and the disabled. But we must also fight with everything we've got to keep protections for those with pre-existing conditions in place & not allow a reversal of the ACA's end to lifetime & annual caps.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Many families register on first-come, first-served lists for aid, equipment, home care and other services. But these lists can stretch more than 10 years. And because Texas declined to expand Medicaid, some lists stretch to thousands of names.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: This President has turned his back on this country, on our democracy, on accountability and justice for what happened in 2016 and what we face in 2018.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We all have to pick a side. I pick people. That’s why we’re not taking a dime from PACs or corporations. That’s why we’re showing up everywhere, all 254 counties, listening to and standing up for everyone. All people, all the time.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: It’s pharmaceutical corporations vs. people (high prices & no accountability). Private prison corporations vs people (mandatory minimums). Internet service corporations vs people (ending net neutrality). Baby formula corporations vs people (UN resolution on breastfeeding).

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Those who are politically connected (corporations like Purdue) are protected from accountability and people suffer as a result. They buy influence and outcomes through lobbying, PAC contributions and sympathetic political appointees.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Meanwhile street levels dealers go to prison. If low level offenders (disproportionately black) are going to prison so should the corporate executives who created the problem in the first place.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: A reminder that the press is not the enemy of the people but the best defense against tyranny. A reminder that thousands of children are still separated from their parents after being taken in our name. And a reminder that we must keep up the pressure until families are reunited.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: At a time when unions are under attack, let's not forget that they are the backbone of our workforce. Critical to bringing more Texans into better, higher paying jobs. Essential to making our communities, businesses, and economy stronger.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Wrapping up more than 1,000 miles on the road. Enjoyed seeing you this past week in:  🚙San Antonio 🚙Houston 🚙Pasadena 🚙Rosenberg 🚙Austin 🚙Hillsboro 🚙Granbury 🚙Pantego 🚙DeSoto 🚙Hutchins  🚙Farmers Branch 🚴‍♂️Dallas 🚙North Richland HIlls Feeling energized & grateful!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let's remember that it's the people who make this nation a Democracy. It's our fellow Texans, Americans across the country. Not the corporations, not the PACs, not the special interests.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We've held more than a dozen running town halls across the state. Tomorrow morning, trying something a bit different. A biking town hall in Dallas. Bring your bikes & helmets, and meet at 8 in the parking lot off Mockingbird Lane, "White Rock Lake Parking" Hope to see you there!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Agricultural mainstays like cotton, grain sorghum, soybeans, and wheat are all under direct attack.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Texas has likewise borne the brunt of Trump's steel and aluminum tariffs.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The impact on agriculture and our energy industry is greater than what's being felt in any other state.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Saturday at 9am. Les Zieger Park (400 Eagle Dr) Hope to see you there!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We must meet these challenges with urgency, strength, and determination. We must not become complacent. As President Johnson said on this date in 1964, "My fellow citizens, we have come now to a time of testing. We must not fail."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The march continues at a time when disparities remain in homeownership, employment, and access to capital. When white families have 10 times more wealth than black families. When the unemployment rate is 2X higher for blacks than whites in Texas.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The march continues at a time when a child’s ZIP code still determines their academic future. When we have a school-to-prison pipeline that leaves black students nearly 4X as likely to be suspended. A graduation rate that finds white students far more likely to receive a diploma.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The march continues at a time when our state implements laws that knowingly make it more difficult for African-American and Latino voters to cast their ballots. When gerrymandering intentionally draws people out of their democracy based on their race and ethnicity.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: But 54 years later, we know the Civil Rights Act is not yet fully realized. We know that disparities remain in access to the ballot, access to high-quality public education, access to higher education, access to capital and high-wage jobs, access to equality in our communities.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "It shall be an unlawful employment practice for an employer to fail or refuse to hire or to discharge any individual, or otherwise to discriminate against any individual...because of such individual's race, color, religion, sex, or national origin"

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "Desegregation means the assignment of students to public schools and within such schools without regard to their race, color, religion, or national origin"

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "The Commission shall investigate allegations in writing under oath or affirmation that certain citizens of the United States are being deprived of their right to vote and have that vote counted by reason of their color, race, religion, or national origin"

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "All persons shall be entitled to the full and equal enjoyment of the goods, services, facilities and privileges, advantages, and accommodations of any place of public accommodation, without discrimination or segregation on the ground of race, color, religion or national origin."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "in public facilities and public education, to extend the Commission on Civil Rights, to prevent discrimination in federally assisted programs, to establish a Commission on Equal Employment Opportunity"

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The law was intended, "to enforce the constitutional right to vote, to confer jurisdiction upon the district courts of the US to provide injunctive relief against discrimination in public accommodations, to authorize the AG to institute suits to protect constitutional rights"

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Signing the legislation, President Johnson said, "This Civil Rights Act is a challenge to all of us to go to work in our communities and our States, in our homes and in our hearts, to eliminate the last vestiges of injustice in our beloved country."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The Civil Rights Act was signed into law 54 years ago. It was the people -- marching, sitting at lunch counters, being sprayed with fire hoses, bitten by dogs, shedding the blood -- who applied the pressure that formed the political will to force this onto the president's desk.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: This piece by @_franciscocantu puts recent administration policies into a much larger perspective. Necessary for us to understand if we are going to change the practices that have led to so much death and suffering now & for decades before.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Hope to see you in San Antonio tonight! We'll be meeting up at 6:00 at Burleson Yard (430 Austin Street).

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Thinking of the families of those killed in Maryland and the newsteam at the Capital Gazette who remind us that reporters across the country -- including those at local papers throughout Texas -- are not the enemy of the people. We must meet this devastating news with action.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The number of adults apprehended with children so far during FY 2018 is actually 15% lower than the number of adults arrested with children during the same period in FY 2017. The number of unaccompanied children arrested is also down from last year.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We must urgently address imbalances in our criminal justice system. Start by ending mandatory minimums for minor drug offenses, ending the fed. prohibition on marijuana, ending cash bail, stopping the use of private prisons, and providing an environment that welcomes re-entry.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We know that our criminal justice system has created a cycle that puts a disproportionate amount of people of color in jail. African Americans and whites use drugs at similar rates, but the imprisonment rate of African Americans for drug charges is almost 6 times that of whites.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: After today, this race to represent Texas in the Senate matters more than ever.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We have to match his strength, optimism, determination with a commitment to addressing the persistent inequities in housing, transportation, access to capital & jobs that pay a living wage that are holding too many back. We have to invest in all of our communities, in all people.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "It's difficult, but hey, it's life, you know? We either deal with it, or we don't,” Crowley said. “I'm dealing with it the best way I can, and that's to keep going forward and keep staying positive."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: He starts his shift at 4:30pm. When it ends at 3am, he makes the 3 hour trip back to the house he rents with his parents. Cuts into time with family, time to sleep, to be healthy, to do hobbies, to do the other things he's meant to do.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: In the last week alone, the Supreme Court has issued close rulings on the president's Muslim ban, on workers’ rights, on voting rights, on gerrymandering, and on a woman’s right to choose. The stakes for this nomination couldn't be higher. We have to get this right.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: It means a new justice who will safeguard the rights of the LGBTQ community. Finally get big money out of politics. End gerrymandering. And ensure every single person coming before that highest court is treated with respect and dignity.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: This means defending and expanding civil rights, voting rights, and workers' rights. It means protecting a woman's right to choose. And upholding protections for those with pre-existing conditions who can finally see a doctor and get the care they need.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Justice Kennedy's retirement opens up a lifetime appointment to the Supreme Court. Any nomination to that seat must live up to the words written above the steps of the highest court in the land, "equal justice under law."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: It's time to end the broken system of cash bail. Nobody should be in jail because they're poor.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We shouldn't be a people who ban individuals of one religion from the shores of a country comprised of immigrants the world over. We are a people who mobilize & show up in airports to confront such a ban. We will continue this fight to define our country. We will get this right.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We must end gerrymandering where members of Congress choose their voters instead of the other way around. We should have a non-partisan, non-politician redistricting commission that ends the practice of racial gerrymandering that has drawn people out of their democracy.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We must work towards access to jobs that pay above a living wage, skill training programs, high-quality public schools for ALL kids no matter ZIP code, affordable housing, & the ability to see a doctor by expanding Medicaid in TX & achieving universal, guaranteed health care.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "Our democracy rests on the ability of all individuals, regardless of race, income, or status, to exercise their right to vote. Because our duty is to safeguard that fundamental right, I dissent."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "It does all of this to allow Texas to use electoral maps that, in design and effect, burden the rights of minority voters to exercise that most precious right that is preservative of all rights.”

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Back in Fort Worth for the night and hope to see you tomorrow at our: ➡8:00 Fort Worth running town hall (Ripley Arnold Plaza, 489 N Taylor St) ➡1:30 Plano town hall (Saigling House, 902 E 16th St) ➡3:30 Flower Mound town hall (Community Activity Center, 1200 Gerault Rd)

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: HHS unable to answer: if total number of families apprehended is down over last year; if total number of unaccompanied kids is up only 4%, then why are we keeping kids longer? Avg stay in detention for kids has gone from 34 days to 56 days. Many kids staying longer than that.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: I met 7 girls who had just arrived at Tornillo this morning. They’ve been in detention for weeks at other locations. Made the journey on their own, hoping to join family here in the U.S.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: What HHS/ORR could not tell me is why they share info about the sponsors (family in the U.S.) for these kids with ICE — the agency tasked with deporting undocumented migrants. Before a kid is placed they get immigration status on everyone in the sponsor’s household.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: I met officials from HHS & contractor who built Tornillo tent city (BCFS) for these kids. They agreed that this crisis was imposed by the Trump administration - that the tent camps at Tornillo would never have been built had Trump not taken kids from their parents at the border.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: I met children who had been in detention for over 3 months; kids whose parents had already been deported back to Guatemala; kids who had no idea when or if they’d see their parents again.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: I was able to visit the children being held in Tornillo. While I am grateful to those who are caring for these kids, the bottom line is that taking kids from their parents and failing to reunite them afterwards is cruel and inhumane. Now we need to make sure it’s un-American.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Whether in local papers or in national outlets, each piece of reporting about family separation has forced our country to face this inhumanity head on. A reminder that the press is more important than ever. Not the enemy of the people, but the best defense against tyranny.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Joining @chrislhayes at 6:00 MT/7:00 CT to give an update on the inhumane practice of child separation and discuss the urgent work that remains to reunify kids with their parents. Hope you'll tune in.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: While 99% of participants attended their ICE check-ins and appointments, a full 100% attended their court hearings. That's according to DHS' Office of Inspector General.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The family case management program only cost $36 a day per family compared to $319 per person indefinitely kept in detention.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Instead of indefinitely keeping families in cages and camps, the family case management program offered a different, more humane path: requiring asylum seekers to check in for their appointments. 99% of participants successfully attended their court appearances and ICE check-ins.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: There are currently private prisons and private immigrant detention centers that have established massive political action committees (PACs). We should end all three.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Looking at this executive order, how does it reunite kids with their parents?

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We marched, called, stood up and spoke out because we believed America to be a place that doesn't take kids from their moms and dads. But we also believe America to be a place that doesn't indefinitely detain families & children in camps. If we don't continue to act, it will be.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let's immediately reunite separated families. But let's also refuse to be a nation that indefinitely locks away these families in cages for doing what any of us would do for our own children. For seeking refuge in a country comprised of immigrants & asylum seekers the world over.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Welcome home Olivia!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: An update since returning from Sunday's march to Tornillo: We've formally introduced legislation that would end the practice of family separation. H.R. 6135 now has over 190 co-sponsors in the House. Companion legislation in the Senate currently has 49 members signed on.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: My honor to hear @CGHollins and @amanda4houston tonight. Two leaders who are out in front and taking charge in their incredible community.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: An update since returning from the border: I'm an original co-sponsor on legislation that would end the practice of family separation. Working with other members of Congress, it looks like our bill will be introduced next week.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: “America was not built on fear. America was built on courage, on imagination and an unbeatable determination to do the job at hand.” We, the people of Texas ,  are the people President Truman was talking about. We're more than a match for this moment. Ready to do the job at hand.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Enough is enough. We are the wealthiest, most powerful nation. Now taking kids from their parents and turning our back to asylum seekers. This requires immediate action. I'm going to the border to get answers and confront this head on. I know that we are better than this.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: If you want to take away healthcare from millions with pre-existing conditions, go ask the people. Have reps go back to their state, face their constituents, and get their permission. I remember what happened last summer when that vote came before congress. The people stopped it.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Late last night, the House voted to cut $7 billion from the Children's Health Insurance Program. The theory was that this would reduce "wasteful" & "unnecessary" spending. The ability for 400,000 Texas kids to see a doctor is not a waste and it is certainly necessary. Voted no.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Dallas! We'll be celebrating our campaign's 254 county journey with a Beers For Texas event tonight at the Foundry (2303 Pittman Street). Hope you'll join us at 5:30. See you soon!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: You're 100% right. And for Black women in Texas, the rate is double. It's unconscionable.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Pregnancy is considered a pre-existing condition. So prior to the Affordable Care Act's provision protecting those with pre-existing conditions, women were frequently denied health care coverage because of it. Let's not go back.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The number of Texans finally receiving care thanks to this provision includes more than 780,000 people in Harris, 455,000 people in Dallas, 386,000 people in Parker & Tarrant, and 321,000 people in Bexar. Big reason why we've seen our uninsured rate drop since the ACA was passed.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: In the memory of James Byrd Jr., in the memory of Matthew Shepard, in the memory of those killed in hate crimes before and after their time, we must continue the march for civil rights, equal rights, and a more just America where we are all treated with dignity and respect.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: For it's never enlightened members of Congress or presidents who've gotten the hard things done. It's the people who've applied the pressure that has formed the political will to force them to get the right thing done. We see that in every civil rights fight of our history.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: My colleague John Lewis reminds us of something Dr King used to say: there is nothing more powerful than the rhythm of marching feet. For James & Matthew, advocates marched on, accepting they might fail at first but knowing their incremental progress would eventually cause change

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: So in 2009 with a new president, they tried again. Though opposed by some Texas reps, it passed the House. It went to the Senate. Newly appointed AG Eric Holder testified in favor. With 5 members crossing the aisle, it passed. On Oct 28, President Barack Obama signed it into law.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: It failed in 2001, 2004, 2005. In 2007, it passed the House but failed in the Senate. When it finally passed the Senate, it received a veto threat from the president and eventually failed again. But advocates across the country refused to give up. Continued marching for progress.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: To remember Byrd and address what had occurred, there were efforts to pass the Matthew Shepard and James Byrd Jr. Hate Crimes Prevention Act. For years, it faced sharp opposition in Congress including from Texas reps, senators, and our current Attorney General Jeff Sessions.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "Veterans suffer chronic severe pain at rates disproportionately higher than their civilian counterparts (roughly 40% higher according to the National Institutes of Health), helping to explain why the opioid crisis has hit veterans at a rate two times the national average."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "Never mind that medical cannabis is now legal in 30 states, or that its medicinal value is recognized by health experts such as the American College of Physicians, the American Public Health Assoc, & the American Nurses Assoc as a safer alternative to many legal treatments."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: "While VA physicians are quick to prescribe powerful drug cocktails (opiates & benzodiazepines) in response to service-related conditions, the federal government continues to deny veterans legal access to a demonstrably safer alternative treatment option — medical cannabis."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Alright Olivia!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: A reminder that instead of allowing profits and corporations to control decision making and care, we need to achieve guaranteed universal healthcare for every single one of us. So that no person is priced out. And so we are all well enough to contribute to our full potential.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: In these stories & the many more that still need to be uncovered, the heroes are the patients, the parents, the families, & the caregivers who never give up. Who give a voice to the voiceless & fight with everything they've got to be treated with the dignity we all deserve.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: In Kosse, Marta looked for a psychiatrist for her 12-year-old foster son whose previous provider had retired. Off his medication for weeks, the boy threatened a sibling with a knife and had a mental breakdown at school. Needed to see a doctor but the wait was 6 months.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Part 3: The companies TX hires & pays billions to care for its sickest citizens have been overstating the number of doctors & specialists available to treat them. DMN called every doctor asking if they could schedule a new-patient appointment for a foster child. Only 9% could.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: In San Antonio, Heather was nearly completely paralyzed. She found joy in being visited by nurses. But then the company TX paid to manage her care cut the hours of her nurses. She was alone for 17 hours a day, unable to move, and in pain. All to save the company a few bucks.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Part 2: Texas used to pay for long-term nursing home care directly, writing checks to doctors & home-care agencies. But now our state turns over many of its health programs to private companies, allowing corporations to profit as they skimp on essential care for disabled adults.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: But the company received no sanctions or fines. In fact, Texas handed them tens of thousands more medically fragile kids to care for in 2017. They received a brand new contract worth more than $440 million a year.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: In Mesquite, D’ashon was born 3 months early, unable to breathe on his own. But with proper care, he was doing better. Then a health care company decided he didn’t need round-the-clock nursing care. The decision would save them as much as $500/day. It cost D’ashon everything.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Part 1: TX pays companies billions to arrange care for foster children, disabled children, chronically sick children. Every $ they don’t spend on care can be used to pay millions in executive bonuses. TX knows companies are skimping on care to make profits but failed to stop it.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Representatives should be accountable to those they're sworn to serve. I hold an El Paso town hall every month. A veterans town hall every quarter. Each one public & in person where any person can ask any question, share any ideas, give any criticism. Today, we held our 9⃣6⃣th.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: I don't think you can be too gay to buy a cake. I don't think you can be too gay to open your caring family to one of TX's 30,000 kids in the foster care system. Let's end this discrimination. Let's pass the Equality Act. Let's ensure equal justice under law for LGBTQ Americans.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: If we are to be engaged in nations across the world tonight, we should have a full understanding of how our decisions are taking the lives of civilians. While questions remain, this report is a first step and will help increase accountability for the impact we're having abroad.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We need a senator who is not afraid to raise these issues with the president. Someone who will stand up to him when he is going to hurt Texas jobs and economic growth. Who will be a voice for the 28 million of us who call Texas home. That’s what I want to do.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: It comes down to the fact that TX is among the nation’s most active states for trade. We rank first in exports. $97 billion in exports to Mexico alone. Our communities depend on it -- from agricultural centers to Houston where exports account for nearly one-fifth of the economy.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: In particular, these tariffs and trade wars threaten our small and medium-sized businesses, which make up more than 90% of all Texas exporters. Their customers abroad support more than 3 million jobs across Texas.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Or talk about how the Pecan Capital of the World is right here in Texas. And that our state is the second largest producer of pecans nationwide. Tariffs hitting pecan growers in San Saba and grapefruit growers in the Rio Grande Valley don’t help our state either.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Could explain what sorghum is. That Texas produces more of it than any other state besides Kansas. That China accounts for more than 70% of US sorghum exports and our share of exported sorghum is 25% of the country’s, accounting for $209 million annually.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Those in the Lubbock region know this better than anyone: our share of US-produced cotton actually makes up nearly half of exports to China, valuing $450M annually. It’s our state’s number two commodity behind beef cattle.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Could talk about agriculture. How Texas is a top producer of cotton, wheat, corn, beef, sorghum -- all of which are targeted by tariffs. One Texan said, “you couldn’t have picked a list of commodities that were more representative of our growers.”

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Could point out that Texas imports more steel and aluminum than any other state in the U.S. That we rely upon those metals for a booming energy sector. That these new tariffs will cause layoffs.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: You could start with the fact that Texas is home to the San Antonio-based Toyota manufacturing plant and the company’s new North America HQ in Plano. No automaker will be hit harder by these tariffs. Prices of cars will have to go up.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Texas could be hit harder than any other state by these kinds of tariffs. Trump’s trade policies will devastate our state, businesses, & economy. Senator Cruz should have explained that to the president while they were riding together last month.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: No wonder people think our campaign finance system is rigged when you can make $20,000 in illegal contributions, be charged, plead guilty, be sentenced, and then receive a pardon. We need to get big money out of politics, end PACs, reverse Citizens United, get our Democracy back.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Virginia is about to become the 33rd state to expand Medicaid, ensuring more people can afford to see a doctor and receive the care they need. Texas should be the 34th.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: And no state is hurt more than ours. Texas continues to have the highest uninsured rate as our neighbors are unable to see a doctor & get the care that they need. We must change course and move towards guaranteed universal healthcare coverage.

name: Beto O'Rourke

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: I signed a discharge petition to force a vote on the #DreamAct. Let’s have the discussion, the debate, and the vote. Let's finally end the uncertainty and protect the 200,000 Dreamers in Texas who contribute to our communities each day.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Congratulations to last night's primary winners across our state. Grateful that we had so many strong candidates running this year who helped Texas lead important policy discussions, excite voters, and build for November 6.

name: Beto O'Rourke

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: GO OLIVIA!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Sending strength and love to Olivia and to you and Jacqueline!!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The open dialogue we’ve been having across Texas is missing from Congress. The House and Senate owe this country a real discussion, debate, and vote on these issues. That's how it's supposed to work. I will continue to do my best to meet this crisis with the urgency it deserves.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Texans can use our proud history of gun ownership, gun rights, gun safety, and gun responsibility as a place from which to lead. We can sit down with any person of any party in any place and at any time to figure out how we can make sure that this does not continue to happen.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: They're at the table. They don't have a shortage of ideas: universal background checks, stop the new sale of assault weapons & high-capacity magazines, give federal help to school districts, fully support research on gun violence, improve record sharing, implement Red Flag Laws.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Any question, any hesitation on how to move forward has been answered by gun violence survivors, young people, high school students who are already leading us towards the difficult, important conversation that this country owes them, owes all of us.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Remembering that, we can meet silence with action. Tragedy with common purpose. The disagreements with compromise and consensus that allow us to do better — not perfect but better than what we have today. Shouldn’t be too much to ask for the kids who died in art class, should it?

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: There are 535 members of Congress. Each member responsible for representing the interests of this country, of people, of human beings, of kids. Not responsible for representing PACs or lobbies, corporations or special interests. Not responsible for focusing on the next election.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: My thoughts are with the community of Santa Fe. All Texans are thinking of the students, teachers, and administrators within the Santa Fe ISD, and the law enforcement officers who are quickly responding.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: A quarter of those who I represent in Congress were born in another country. They are not animals.   Texas has the second largest state immigrant population. They are not animals.   Our country is a nation of immigrants. They are not animals.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: I urge Paul Ryan and leadership to finally bring the debate to the House floor. Like the majority of Americans, I support #netneutrality.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Definitely. When running for Congress in 2012, I pledged to host at least one town hall back in El Paso every single month where my constituents could share their ideas, ask questions, and hold me accountable. Just held our 94th. We'll do the same in the Senate.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Our state should expand Medicaid to cover more Texans. Our country should create a public option on the exchanges so Americans have access to affordable coverage. And we should achieve universal, guaranteed quality health care for each and every one of us.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Introducing term limits, outlawing Political Action Committees, ending Citizens United, and putting a stop to gerrymandering are essential to returning power to the people and finally having a government that is responsive to those it purports to serve & represent.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Our legislation would amend the Constitution to cap service at 12 years. A maximum of six two-year terms in the House and two six-year terms in the Senate. We have term limits for most offices, from the presidency to the Mayor of El Paso. Let's have term limits for Congress too.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Just joined my colleagues in introducing bipartisan legislation to limit the number of years a member of Congress can serve. We must end the perpetual re-election of Reps and Senators, and start bringing new voices, ideas, and perspectives to the Capitol.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: At another town hall, a veteran came forward & said that without an alternative to the opioids he was previously being prescribed by the VA, he's buying heroin on the street. We've got to allow doctors to prescribe what's in the best interests of our veterans, including cannabis.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: At a time when it's legal in 29 states, veterans in Texas have come up to me at our town hall meetings and said that while it is the only thing that eases their pain, they are treated as a criminal in our state for seeking it out.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Proud to see the VA Medicinal Cannabis Research Act pass the Veterans' Affairs Committee. As a cosponsor of this bipartisan legislation, I know it'll promote research into the safety & use of cannabis for veterans who have been diagnosed with chronic pain, PTSD, & other injuries.

name: Beto O'Rourke

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We need universal background checks in this country. No more loopholes. Common sense, supported by most Americans, and will save lives in our communities.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: It will be to our loss and our lasting shame if we allow the 200,000 Dreamers in Texas to be deported as they continue contributing to our communities, state, and country. We need to pass the Dream Act.

tweet: If we need a new AUMF then let’s debate it and involve the American people. It will be a frustratingly deliberate, sober process. As intended by the Constitution. We should not go into war lightly or infinitely.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: With the first report due May 1, we'll soon have a better understanding of civilian casualties, and how we can increase accountability for the impact we're having abroad.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: So I offered a provision to require an annual public report on civilian deaths. Worked across the aisle to pass it through committee. Got it through the full House in a bipartisan fashion & the Senate was able to do the same. Sent to the president's desk, he signed it into law.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: For decades, there has been a lack of accountability when it comes to civilian casualties caused by our actions abroad. If we are to be engaged in nations across the world tonight, we should have a full understanding of how our decisions are taking the lives of civilians.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We will not allow the VA to be privatized. If we want to fulfill our commitment to those who’ve served, we must invest in the VA, ensure that it delivers the best care and service possible.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We all want the next VA Secretary to be successful. Their success means we are better able to serve the women and men who put their lives on the line for our country.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Beyond serving those who put their lives on the line for this country, the VA Secretary leads the nation's second largest department. The nomination, vetting, and confirmation process for this individual should be done with the care our veterans deserve.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We're a bold, confident, big-hearted people. Above the small, petty scare tactics. Don't need to ban individuals of one religion from the shores of a country comprised of immigrants the world over. Don't need to call for patrolling Muslim neighborhoods.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: In the midst of a suicide crisis that claims the lives of more than 20 veterans a day, the VA needs a Secretary who is fully committed to serving those who put their lives on the line for our country. This isn't a responsibility that can be taken lightly.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Today, another senator pledged to no longer accept corporate PAC money. A step in the right direction for our democracy and a sign that our campaign is already changing the system. We are running this without any PACs, corporations, or special interests. Just people.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: This is part of a larger trend. From trying to privatize public education through vouchers and attempting to role back campus sexual assault policies, DeVos continues to take the Department in the wrong direction. She was confirmed by a one vote margin. This Senate seat matters.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: First Lady Barbara Bush was dedicated to our state and devoted to our country. I'm joining Texans and Americans everywhere in keeping her family in our thoughts during this time.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: President Obama had it spot on when he said that Jackie Robinson exemplified our uniquely American story of fighting for change, "We are Jackie Robinson, enduring scorn and spiked cleats and pitches coming straight to his head, and stealing home in the World Series anyway."

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We join Texans across the state in keeping the First Lady and the entire Bush family in our thoughts.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: I have joined with colleagues from both sides of the aisle to end the open authorization for endless war. We cannot put the burden of our foreign policy, the problems of the world, soley on the backs of our service members.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Re comments on endless war: we are at war all the time and to what effect? I was a senior in high school when Bush 1 announced US military in Iraq. Have used military force in that country every year and every administration since, no end in sight.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: You are absolutely right — presidents of both parties have done this and members of Congress from both parties have been complicit.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We may decide that use of chemical weapons requires a military response. But we must decide that lawfully, as a country, through our representatives in Congress. Holding the president to the law & constitution doesn’t mean we condone Assad nor does it preclude military response.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Only the American people through their representatives in Congress can decide to attack another country that has not attacked us.

name: Beto O'Rourke

name: Beto O'Rourke

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Instead of taking healthcare away from even more people in a state that already leads the country in the uninsured rate, let's work towards ensuring that every Texan can see a doctor.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We can't let the pharmaceutical industry be the priority, no matter how deep their pockets may be (another reason why I introduced the No PAC Act). Let's put access to affordable healthcare & prescriptions first in this country.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: That's why I'm an original cosponsor on HR 4138 & HR 4117, which allow Medicare to negotiate drug pricing and prevent brand name drug companies from paying off generics to delay the introduction of their cheaper drugs.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Grateful for you, your courage and the inspiration that you and Victor and other amazing families like yours give to all of us. Look forward to seeing you in North Texas before long!

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We have to meet the pettiness, the meanness, the SMALLNESS, the shameful "us vs. them" mentality of our current leaders -- and our current government -- with the confidence, the courage and the STRENGTH of the people of this country.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: On to the aspirational things that only a healthy country can achieve -- winning the fight to reverse climate change, finding a cure to Alzheimer's, or AIDS or cancer. Or all of them. Leading humanity in the truly great challenges before us, without fear.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Or what if we could respond to the clear moral choice before us and make sure every kid who needs to can see a doctor, a therapist, receive medication because we no longer debate the authorization for CHIP or quibble about expanding Medicaid?

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Like standing up not only for the Dreamers, but also their parents, who decided to leave a hometown, a country that they knew, a language that was familiar -- to come here, to choose us, to give their kids a better chance, to contribute to the success of our country.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: But we’ve also got to think beyond funding the government for a full year (as high a bar as that might seem for Congress right now) and reach for something even bigger. Aspirational. Inspiring.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Those who serve this country in uniform expect it of us. Defense Secretary Mattis has talked about the damage done to the readiness of our service members when we fail to fully fund our obligations, and instead limp along under these spending-gap bills.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We can't run government by crisis, lurching from one 30-day funding extension to the next. We also can't neglect the moral questions before us, in the hope that someone else at some point in the future will decide them on our behalf.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: But it's not good enough to simply rail against #CitizensUnited. We've got to act. It's why I introduced the No PAC Act. It's why I'm running our campaign without a penny from PACs. It's why I'm putting my trust in the people of Texas not the pocketbooks of special interests.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Helps explain why Congress is captured, corroded, and corrupted by special interests to an extent that we've never seen before. Corporations and PACs are literally purchasing outcomes.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: 8 years ago, Supreme Court ruled in #CitizensUnited that corporations were people and money was speech. This unleashed a dangerous amount of spending by PACs, corporations, and special interests at the direct expense of our Democracy.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: 400,000 children and pregnant women in Texas rely on CHIP to see a doctor. 200,000 Dreamers contribute to our state's success each day. We, the most powerful country in the world, can do the right thing by both.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Shutdown is a failure in leadership: Speaker who can’t bring a full year’s funding bill to the floor. President who rescinded DACA & won’t honor the agreement made to save it. Members of Congress who enable this and fail to insist on full year funding & keeping families together

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: So let's move with the example of this morning. Let's bring all sides into the room, let's listen, let's share ideas, let's hold true to our values and ensure we do the right thing on DACA. All of that is within our power to do. And it's the correct path forward for our country.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Believe it or not, there is actually bipartisan agreement on the need to keep the government running and pass a long-term funding bill. There is agreement on the DREAM Act, on funding CHIP, on the important and timely things we need to do.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: It also continued the reckless course of short-term funding, falling short on our commitment to the Dept of Defense, VA, CBP , and all those who serve. Let's fund them not weeks at a time but  for the rest of the year so we can address the challenges & opportunities before us.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: For starters, it failed to reflect even the faintest input from members of both parties. Republican leadership in both the House and Senate gave Democrats no opportunity to participate in the discussions.That’s not how Congress should work.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: I wish I could say the results were instant, that Congress took our lead and held a bipartisan discussion on government funding by the afternoon. But that wasn't the case. Instead, there was a party-line vote on a short-term funding bill for the FOURTH time since Oct. I voted no.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Started today by sitting down with No Labels and the Problem Solvers Caucus -- Democrats and Republicans from both the House and the Senate sitting across the table from one another, talking, listening, and most importantly, working together.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: All at a time when we’re spending $20 billion a year to secure the border, where there are already 600 miles of walls and fences, where we already have twice as many border patrol agents than in 2004 with 20,000 continuing to make sure we are safe. Let's keep the facts in mind.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: It takes our eye off of real problems, real threats, and therefore makes us LESS SAFE. At a time of record safety along the border, when we have the lowest levels of apprehensions along the US-Mexico border in recent history, not zero but less than zero net Mexican migration.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: El Paso is also home to more than 9,000 Dreamers, young Americans who make us a better, safer, stronger community. Let’s focus on keeping them here, contributing to our success... instead of building walls that we don’t need.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Walls have nothing to do with it. We have been ranked 1st, 2nd, or 3rd safest city in the U.S. for 20 years (including years before wall). On top of great law enforcement, our safety is connected to being a community of immigrants. We treat eachother with respect and dignity.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The audacity to believe that every person can see a doctor, every kid can get a quality education, fighting hunger, delivering dignity and equality to all.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Stop the process where members of Congress choose their voters instead of the other way around. Stop drawing people out of their democracy. Let's take the lead in Texas.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: The way that Trump talks about Mexicans, Haitians and Central Americans is not too different from how racists and “America first” proponents were talking about Irish, Italians and Polish not too long ago. We will once again overcome this anti-immigrant nativism.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Looking forward to discussing this and more on CNN’s @NewDay tomorrow (Thursday) morning at 6:45 ET/5:45 CT. I hope you’ll tune in if you’re an early riser.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: This is all to say that we need a clean Dream Act. It not only has bipartisan support in Congress but it has bipartisan support across the country. 86% of voters overall and 75% among Republicans.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: While the country would lose between $283 billion and $430 billion, Texas would be the second hardest hit state with an economic loss of $6 billion/year. This after our state had the largest GDP growth in the nation during the first quarter of last year.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: And Dreamers are working hard for their success. 76% are currently employed. An additional 20% are not working but are enrolled in school. The right-leaning Cato Institute found that the economic loss of Dreamers would be measured not in the millions but in the billions.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Let's be on the right side of history for 200,000 Dreamers in Texas and the 9,000 eligible DACA recipients I represent in El Paso. They contribute to the fact that our binational community has been ranked as the 1st, 2nd, or 3rd safest city in the country for more than a decade.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We’ve got to have the courage of our convictions in memory of Alonso Guillen, a Dreamer who died while saving his fellow Texans from the destructive flooding of Hurricane Harvey. Those he saved needed him.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We’ve got to do right by Melissa who is finishing up her final semester of a mathematics degree. Here since age five, she is making our community safer as an intern with the Labor Justice Commission protecting Texans from wage theft and human trafficking. We need her.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: We’ve got to do the right thing for Texas Tech student Saba who was brought to our country at age 11 and is now finishing up her PhD in mathematical biology, ready to help understand diseases and even explore new cures. We need her.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: 400,000 kids in Texas are about to lose the ability to see a doctor, a therapist, a nurse — the caregivers  who will be able to improve or save their lives. Republicans in Congress have prioritized tax cuts over Children’s Health Insurance Program (CHIP).

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: All of that and too much more. Only 33% of Americans approve of the plan. Even fewer (21%) think they will be better off if it becomes law. Texans are paying attention. Texans know what's happening. And Texans won't forget.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Thanks to our junior senator, $500 million in tax payer money will be pulled out of our public schools to benefit wealthy parents and private schools. No wonder teachers are outraged.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Say you're lucky enough to still be insured, you'll see premiums go up an average of $1,730 a year. So much for a tax break if you're paying more for the ability to see a doctor.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Causes 13 million more people to be uninsured. One million in Texas alone, the least insured state in the union.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Sends 83% of tax breaks to the top 1%. At the expense of 86 million middle class households who will see tax increases (that's HALF of American middle class families!).

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: This will hurt our public school students, our public school teachers, librarians and nurses. It will result in more inequality in our country. Not good for our country, not good for Texas. It’s another reason I will vote NO on the tax bill today.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: Cruz’s private school give away will cost taxpayers $500 million to subsidize wealthy parents at the expense of public school students.

tweet: For someone who claims to represent Texas, I'm not hearing a lot about our state in tonight's #TaxDebate. Like how 50% of the cuts in TX go to the top 1%.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: It's been our junior senator leading their charge. We must strengthen protections for customers, not corporations. Hard sell if you're taking their money by the millions. We have a chance to do the right thing.

name: Beto O'Rourke
tweet: You stopped the ACA repeal in July. Lots of politicians will take credit. But it was the people of this country providing the public pressure that formed the political will to do the right thing. We can do it again.
